s a `ParameterizedType` argument that is a `GenericArrayType`. For valid Java source fields, those cases have a component type such as a `TypeVariable` or another non-`Class` `Type`, not a concrete `Class`. Morphia 1.3.2 immediately casts that component to `Class` before the uncovered `Array.newInstance(...)` call:\n\n```java\nfinal Class arrayType = (Class) ((GenericArrayType) paramType).getGenericComponentType();\nreturn Array.newInstance(arrayType, 0).getClass();\n```\n\nSo supported Java field shapes that enter the branch fail at the cast and never reach line 201. Covering line 201 would require an artificial/non-javac field signature or runtime class definition/loading, which would violate the Native Image testing rules and the requirement to cover supported behavior only.\n\nCurrent focused coverage already reaches the other 8 `ReflectionUtils` dynamic-access sites via `ReflectionUtilsTest.java`; the remaining site should be left uncovered with this explanation.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_097ee74e7dcbebe5016a41e37f341c8197992f8b9b9da8e2b6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 7333, "output": 1182, "cacheRead": 48640, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57155, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782702960078, "responseId": "resp_097ee74e7dcbebe5016a41e370a44c8197a4930a7d789efe53"}, "toolResults": []}
